07/11/2006
BOURGAS, Bulgaria -- US Ambassador to Bulgaria John Beyrle said on Monday (November 6th) that the country's upcoming EU membership would boost its position in NATO, as well as its bilateral partnership with the United States.
In a speech at Bourgas Free University, he also stressed the importance of a strong Bulgarian economy, noting that after its EU entry, Bulgaria would become part of US-EU trade relations and would attract more US investment.
(Monitor - 07/11/06;
Darik - 06/11/06)
